<c74object name='dk.slicecurve' category='' module='dataknot'>
    <digest>Divides a normalized space into equal or irregularly-spaced slices
</digest>
    <description>The <o>dk.slicecurve</o> object takes incoming numbers (either as jump indices or MIDI note numbers) and converts these into slices of a normalized space. These can be evenly spaced or with a curve applied to create irregularly-spaced slices.ch using a single float from a controller or UI object.
</description>
    <discussion>This was adapted from an early monome app called Block Party that made use of non-linear distribution of slices on a grid. The implementation here allows you to use arbitrary curve values, rather than an option of fixed ones.
</discussion>

	<metadatalist>
		<metadata name='author'>Rodrigo Constanzo, FluCoMa Project</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Machine Learning</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Audio Analysis</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Onset Detection</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Corpus Playback</metadata>
	</metadatalist>

